{{Infobox | name = SensUs | above = SensUs Student Competition | image = [[File:SensUsLogoRedTransp.jpg|frameless|]] | label1 = Contest date | data1 = September 6-7, 2019 | label2 = Frequency | data2 = Annual | label3 = Location | data3 = Eindhoven, The Netherlands | label4 = First year | data4 = 2016 | label5 = Contact | data5 = contact@sensus.org | label6 = Website | data6 = [http://www.sensus.org www.sensus.org] | label7 = Livestream | data7 = [https://digital.sensus.org/ digital.sensus.org] | label8 = Photos | data8 = [https://www.flickr.com/photos/158504404@N02/albums Flickr] | label9 = Videos | data9 = [https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC0jKe6AdmY5K5QdPNcY8C-w/videos Youtube] }}
{{Orphan|date=April 2016}}
SensUs <ref>[http://www.sensus.org/ SensUs website]</ref> is the annual international [[student competition]] on molecular [[biosensor]]s for health.<ref group=a>A [[biosensor]] is a compact device that interacts with a biological system to acquire a signal for diagnostic or monitoring purposes. A molecular biosensor is a biosensor with a molecular interaction as a central aspect. It is an analytical device with a molecular recognition element and with a transduction principle that turns the biomolecular interaction into a measurable signal. Molecular biosensors operate on samples taken from the body (in-vitro testing e.g. using a drop of blood) or are worn on or inside the body (for real-time in-vivo sensing).</ref> Multidisciplinary student teams from universities worldwide design and build biosensing systems, and demonstrate their prototypes and business models during a final public contest event. The competition stimulates education and innovation in the field of biosensing, with a worldwide scope. The long term aim is to improve the quality of life of patients.
[[File:SensUs 2018 teams and organization.jpg|thumb|Photo of SensUs organization and Teams 2018]]
== Approach of the competition == Each year, SensUs adresses a different healthcare theme and a corresponding biomarker. The participating teams develop biosensors that can measure the selected biomarker. The teams have the same functional end goal, but develop creative solutions and unique biosensor prototypes. The prototypes are shown, shared and discussed at the annual SensUs contest event. SensUs is an international platform for learning and innovation in the field of molecular biosensors for healthcare applications.
== Next Edition == === SensUs 2019 ===
The theme of SensUs 2019 is Rheumatoid Arthritis and the molecule to be detected is [[Adalimumab]] (brand name Humira). Adalimumab is a biological drug that binds to TNF-alpha, a pro-inflammatory cytokine. The overexpression of this cytokine plays an important rolein rheumatoid arthritis. Many patients do not respond to treatment with Adalimumab or lose response during treatment. A biosensor for Adalimumab could detect this at an early stage and help save unnecessary costs. Worldwide annual sales of Adalimumab are more than 10 billion US dollars.<ref>[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adalimumab Adalimumab]</ref>
A list of the participating universities in SensUs 2019 can be found below. The finals of SensUs 2019 will take place on the 6th and 7th of September 2019 in Eindhoven, the Netherlands.
