The '''Student Study Service''' ([[Indonesian language|indonesian]]: ''Kuliah Kerja Nyata'' or KKN) is a concept of linking academic study with the practical experience of [[community service]].<ref name="eric">{{cite journal|title= Service-Learning in Duta Wacana Christian University: Past, Present, and Future States|author= Krisnawati, Lucia Dwi|journal= New Horizons in Education|volume= 57 |issue=3 |pages= 74–81 |date= December 2009|issn= 1683-1381|url= http://eric.ed.gov/?id=EJ893705|}}</ref> Since 1973, KKN has been integrated into the higher education curriculum for Indonesian universities, and it became one of higher education's threefold responsibilities besides teaching and conducting researches.<ref name="eric"/> Through the KKN program, the students are expected to share their knowledge and help local people to improve their lives and motivate them toward self-development.<ref name="jak">{{cite web|title= University students to join national community service|publisher= The Jakarta Post|accessdate= 28 April 2014| url= http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2013/10/26/university-students-join-national-community-service.html}}</ref>

